{{演化生物学}}

'''演化語言學'''或'''達爾文語言學'''是一種[[社會生物學|社會生物學]]取徑的[[語言學|語言學]]研究<ref name=Gontier_2012>{{cite journal |last=Gontier |first=Nathalie |date=2012 |title=Selectionist approaches in evolutionary linguistics: an epistemological analysis |url= |journal=International Studies in the Philosophy of Science |volume=26 |issue=1 |pages=67–95 |doi=10.1080/02698595.2012.653114 |access-date=}}</ref><ref name=McMahon&McMahon_2012>{{cite book|last1=McMahon | first1=April | last2=McMahon | first2=Robert  |year=2012|title=Evolutionary Linguistics|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0521891394|pages=}}</ref>。演化語言學家認為語言學[[演化生物學|演化生物學]]和[[演化心理學|演化心理學]]的次領域。這種研究取徑也與[[演化人類學|演化人類學]]、[[認知語言學|認知語言學]]和[[生物語言學|生物語言學]]有所關連。演化語言學將語言視為[[先天與後天|先天]]的產物，主要關注於語言的生物性[[語言起源|起源]]和語言的發展<ref name=Croft_2008>{{cite journal | last = Croft | first = William |date=October 2008 | title = Evolutionary Linguistics | journal = Annual Review of Anthropology | volume = 37 | pages = 219–234 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.anthro.37.081407.085156 }}</ref>。演化語言學與[[人文主義|人文主義]]取徑相對，特別是[[結構語言學|結構語言學]]<ref name=Croft_1993>{{cite journal |last=Croft |first=William |date=1993 |title=Functional-typological theory in its historical and intellectual context |url= |journal=STUF – Language Typology and Universals |volume=46 |issue=1–4 |pages=15–26 |doi=10.1524/stuf.1993.46.14.15 |access-date=}}</ref>。

該學科較大的一項挑戰是其缺乏實證資料：早期人類語言並無任何[[考古學|考古學]]證據。[[計算系統生物學|計算系統生物學]]與[[人工語言|人工語言]]的[[臨床研究|臨床研究]]常用來填補這一部分的知識空缺。雖然一般認為是生物學形塑了[[大腦|大腦]]對於語言的處理，目前卻無法找到生物學與特定的語言結構或[[普遍文法|語言的普遍性]]的明確連結<ref name=Gibson&Tallerman_2011>{{cite book |editor-last1=Gibson|editor-first1=Kathleen R. |editor-last2=Tallerman|editor-first2=Maggie|title=The Oxford Handbook of Language Evolution |publisher=Oxford University Press |date=2011 |pages= |chapter= | url= | access-date= |isbn= 9780199541119| author-link=}}</ref>。

該領域一直缺乏突破性發展，隨之而來的是許多針的語言的自然本質的討論。有些人認為可將其視為一種[[器官|器官]]<ref name=Anderson&Lightfoot_2002>{{cite book |last1=Anderson|first1=Stephen R. |last2=Lightfoot|first2=David W. |title=The Language Organ: Linguistics as Cognitive Psychology |publisher=Cambridge University Press |date=2003 |pages= |chapter= | url=  | access-date= |isbn= 9780521007832| author-link=}}</ref>或是[[有機體|有機體]]<ref name=VanDriem_2005>{{cite book |last=van Driem |first=George |date=2005 |editor-last1=Minett |editor-first1=James W. | editor-last2=Wang | editor-first2= William S.-Y.| title=Language Acquisition, Change and Emergence: Essays in Evolutionary Linguistics| chapter=The language organism: the Leiden theory of language evolution |url=  |pages=331–340 |isbn= |access-date=}}</ref>。有些人認為語言可視為一種[[晶體|晶體]]<ref name=Chomsky_2015>{{cite book |last=Chomsky |first=Noam |title=The Minimalist Program. 20th Anniversary Edition. |publisher=MIT Press |date=2015 |pages=| url=| access-date= |isbn= 978-0-262-52734-7| author-link=}}</ref>或非晶體式的[[礦物|礦物]]結構<ref name=Bybee&Beckner_2015>{{cite book |last1=Bybee |first1=Joan L. |last2=Beckner |first2=Clay|date=2015 |editor-last1=Heine |editor-first1=Bernd | editor-last2=Narrog | editor-first2=Heiko| title=The Oxford Handbook of Linguistic Analysis| chapter=Usage-Based theory |publisher=Oxford University Press  |pages=953–980 |doi=10.1093/oxfordhb/9780199544004.013.0032 |access-date=}}</ref>，一種基因[[突變|突變]]<ref name=Berwick&Chomsky_2015>{{cite book |last1=Berwick|first1=Robert C. |last2=Chomsky|first2=Noam | title=Why Only Us: Language and Evolution|url=https://archive.org/details/whyonlyuslanguag0000berw|publisher=MIT Press |date=2015  |isbn=9780262034241| author-link=}}</ref>，一種生物[[本能|本能]]<ref name=Pinker_1994>{{cite book |last=Pinker |first=Steven |year=1994 |title=The Language Instinct: How the Mind Creates Language |publisher=Penguin Books |url=http://f.javier.io/rep/books/The-Language-Instinct-How-the-Mind-Creates-Language,-Steven-Pinker.pdf |pages= |isbn=9780140175295 |access-date=2020-03-03 |archive-date=2019-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126174446/http://f.javier.io/rep/books/The-Language-Instinct-How-the-Mind-Creates-Language,-Steven-Pinker.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，一種[[寄生蟲|寄生蟲]]<ref name=Hung_2019>{{cite journal |last=Hung |first=Tzu-wei |date=2019 |title=How did language evolve? Some reflections on the language parasite debate |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/332340618 |journal=Biological Theory |volume=14 |issue= 4|pages=214–223 |doi=10.1007/s13752-019-00321-x |access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref>一種[[複製器|複製器]]的[[群體|群體]]<ref name=Croft_2008 />；甚或是一種[[心智病毒|心智病毒]]。然而目前沒有任何科學證據可以證實上述說法，有些看法亦被視為[[偽科學|偽科學]]<ref name=Schwarz-Friesel_2012>{{cite journal |last=Schwarz-Friesel |first=Monika |date=2012 |title=On the status of external evidence in the theories of cognitive linguistics |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_language-sciences_2012-11_34_6/page/656|journal=Language Sciences |volume=34 |issue=6 |pages=656–664 |doi=10.1016/j.langsci.2012.04.007|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=Polichak_2002>{{cite book |last=Polichak |first=James W. |date=2002|editor-last=Shermer |editor-first=Michael |  title=The Skeptic Encyclopedia of Pseudoscience, Vol. 1| publisher=ABC Clio |chapter=Memes as pseudoscience |url=https://archive.org/details/skepticencyclope00sher|pages=[https://archive.org/details/skepticencyclope00sher/page/664 664]–667 |isbn=1-57607-653-9 |access-date=}}</ref>。

